Jan 20 2009 	Central clean and inexpensive Vegas hotel	This is a great place to stay for the price. The rooms are clean and up to date. The hotel is located almost dead center on the strip, so it makes a good home base for wandering. It is very small but I found this a plus, as it took only about a minute to get from the street to my room. We also caught part of the Big Elvis show which was decent. The only negative is that the hotel is themed as a wild west drinking saloon which can sometimes be a little obnoxious.For roughly the same price or less you can stay at the Imperial Palace, but from what I've heard it is not worth it. If you are on a budget, or don't plan on spending a lot of time in your hotel, stay at Bills.	
