Oct 13 2008	The Pros and Cons of Bill's in a Nutshell	Plenty of good, thorough reviews on this site -- enough for you to see that Bill's is a good bet for your stay in Las Vegas. Here's my take on things, from my 5-night stay in Sept. 2008:The Pros:1. Yes, great location -- you don't have to walk for days to get from your room to the casino or the street -- you will thanks yourself for this2. Unpretentious -- I always felt like I could go and hang downstairs because the crowd was mellow and never too much3. Great rooms -- for $89/nt Sun-Thurs, you get a big room with plenty of space and great, comfortable clean beds4. Room service -- found this to be excellent, food was good5. TV -- the huge flat-screen was a plusThe Cons:1. The room didn't have a coffee maker and there was no mini-fridge, mini-bar, or other amenities. The soaps and shampoos where nice, but I had to ask at one point to be re-filled -- no biggie2. The cable TV selection was average and the pay-per-view movie selection sucked, in my opinion -- just your usual mainstream fare. The porn was so-so, not much variety.3. Internet connection worked but it was $11.99 per day, and was only dial-up -- you should probably find a way to hook up wireless.4. The nearest liquor store was a good 10 minute walk away, but room service does sell over-priced bottles.On the whole, a very good bet for anyone, could very well be the best deal in town for a solid, no-frills, comfortable Las Vegas trip.	
